doc.field: but damn, i miss the sun
how can i truly appreciate you in all your glory without the contrast?
i was born in a culture where anyone out of the ordinary (extraordinary?) was locked away in a dark room, bound in chains.
i knew such a girl, living in a ground floor apartment in the building i called home as a child
i never saw her, but i heard her often when playing with friends – we all knew her indirectly - we just made up stories
the definition of normal - so highly constructed, so limited
what about the extraordinary gifts these not-so-normal individuals possess?
we don't quite honor these until they have long passed – do we?
but without all the crap about new places and such
maybe this place is exactly what keeps me 'normal'
or maybe it's the thought of going far, far away...
